tspan.tspan: Algorithm for adding a new leaf to the top level of the group drawn from the
(logical dependencies:algorithm step label) algorithm step description
(b) Insert the leaf. Call the leaf node L.
(c) Insert a node. Call the node N.
(bc:d) Insert a red edge from N to L.
(ac:e) Insert a blue edge from N to G.
(ac:f) Insert a green edge from N to G.
(def:g) Switch the green node to N
- Step (g) depends on d, e, and f in order to make this algorithm atomic.
Atomicity is nice because it means we can serialize the application state at any
time without having to worry about placing a write lock on it. Every algorithm
which modifies the graph should switch the green node as the very last step.
Moreover, no algorithm should ever remove a node or edge that is reachable
from any node on the tree of green edges.
